      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SOHO GUNSLINGER (6) was far from disgraced in the Riverina Championships, beaten just over 11m in the entires and geldings final last start. The last time he raced here he came from this barrier and scored a win by close 7m over this distance and in the same grade. History could repeat tonight. MESSAGE BANK (8) is a talented three-year-old who comes through the Gold Chalice series at Bathurst where he won his heat before a midfield finish in the final. Can measure up to these. LAYDEN (2) made a strong start for the Jarrod Alchin stable when he worked but proved too tough in a 2.2m win at this venue. Drops in grade but looks well served by a lower draw. DEMON BLUE NZ (4) has had seven weeks off but his best form measures up here while LENNETH (3) draws well and has claims off a second two back at this circuit and distance.",
